text:
Congrats on a great first month to everyone. Watching your collabs together is always fun. Here's hoping the months and even years ahead are even better and that you all can find more time for these adventures. I'm curious to at least try Minecraft someday.

I've been thinking about the character themes of HoloMyth and, perhaps I'm reading too much into this and it's just my imagination going overboard, to me it reminds me of the darker side of the idol world: investigators going through their history, predators from afar getting closer, burning out and being replaced by the younger, going crazy from the voices of the powers that be and fanatics, and death. Again, I'm probably putting too much thought into this, but it seems like it's too clever to just be coincidence; I have to wonder who came up with these particular characters and what they were thinking.

text:
Shaaark Gura! Thank you for picking up one of my favorite games of all time.
A few tips for Best Shark:
1) Overworld hostile mobs only spawn in light level 7 or lower. Lighting up areas which you frequent is one of the best ways to stay safe.
2) Combat! In the 1.19 Combat Update they added cooldown to attacks, where you do less damage if you spam click but you do the full damage if you click rhythmically. There are also combat tricks like attacking while falling to do more damage, or attack while sprinting for more knockback, which is particularly useful vs creepers. 
3) Inventory management! This will help stay productive and achieve the goal of building Atlantis faster. Put things you don't need for your current goal away, have as many free slots to work with as possible. It may be tempting keep all tools on hand or to hoard treasures you find on the way, but sometimes it's better to keep them in a chest you'll return to to focus on the current task.

You're learning fast! I'm looking forward to see what Atlantis look like.

text:
Tips for minecraft:



Shift click something to put it in your hotbar (if there is a slot), shift click something in your hotbar to put it back into your inventory if there's a slot, shift click armor to equip it if there is a slot available. Hold on left mouse button to divide something equally along the slots in your inventory and hold right click to put one in each slot
Diamonds and netherite (ancient debris in the nether) is <Y13
Gold is <Y30 (<Y80 if its a badlands biome)
Press F on something in your hotbar to put it in your off hand (You can duel wield swords, but the offhand does not work, similarly to other tools in the offhand. What you can put are torches when you're mining, blocks when building, or a shield to protect yourself (hold right click but you cannot use your sword when blocking)
To get food effectively, craft a flint and steel (flint from gravel and iron ingot) and burn an animal then use your sword to kill it which causes instant smelting
Do not spam click when killing a mob, there is a cooldown introduced in the combat update so you need to time it to damage a mob effectively. The timer is below your crosshair.
To make your tools better, make an enchantment table. You can surround it with bookcases for better enchants, but you need Lapis Lazuli (fake diamonds as I call it). Try to get silk touch on a pickaxe so you can start removing spawners for mob grinders (for xp and mob drops for example a skeleton farm gets you some bone meal and arrows). You can also enchant books in order to enchant them onto something else, though usually they will come with additional enchants that are not suitable for your tools/armor for example thorns and fire aspect on a book. You can use anvils to try to upgrade certain aspects of a book, however there is a max. Aqua affinity and respiration (max 3) can be enchanted through an anvil onto your helmet in order to mine and breathe better underwater.
To empty your inventory quickly into a chest you can click on a material, hover over the same material still in your inventory or chest and double click to empty everything other than the item you are holding to the chest or your inventory.
A good way to kill endermen for ender pearls which you can teleport using is to build above you (so there's a 2 block height from the ground to your roof) then stare at the endermen so they will be aggravated then kill them. If you do it correctly, the endermen cannot reach you. You can also go into water then try to bow them.
Instead of a railway system, you can get Blue ice and make a long 2 by 2 path and scatter the blue ice in a checkered way so every other block has blue ice in it then put a boat somewhere, ride onto the blue ice, and it will send you going wherever you need to go, although it is quite hard to turn.
You can turn subtitles on in your settings to hear for "Lava pops" which means there is lava nearby so you can be cautious, or try to find diamonds, because diamonds usually spawn near lava pools.
Magma blocks or Soul sand both usually found in the Nether can replenish your breath (shift on magma blocks) or you can use doors and go into the air bubble for breath while underwater.
You can farm bees as a food and block source by placing a campfire or fire (use netherrack to keep fire there forever) to harvest honey bottles using an empty bottle or shears for honeycombs that can craft extra beehives or honeycomb blocks. Use carpet and blocks surrounding campfires to keep the bees safe in case they run into it.
In the nether, you can find blue fire, bastions, gold ore, ancient debris, two types of forests, soul sand and soul blocks, normal fire, gravel, netherrack, magma cubes, magma blocks, ghasts, blazes (for crafting enderpearls into eyes of ender to find the stronghold and beat the boss), wither skeletons, etc. Fire and lava cannot be extinguished unless you do it naturally or using couldrons or potions. You can bring couldrons (iron in an U shape in a crafting table) and pour water buckets into it then jump in to extinguish yourself, but normal water will just evaporate and not spawn. You do not need 14 obsidian to create a portal, instead you can have 10 and remove the corners. You can also use lava source blocks and water to create obsidian (you still need a diamond pickaxe to mine it).

Please like this so Gura can see this, likes do not affect me at all I just want to let her and the team know all this.

text:
Shark fact: Whale sharks, despite their massive ~1.5 meter/5 feet wide mouth, only have throats comparable in size to a moderately sized coin(~20 mm, or less than an inch, in diameter). This is to capitalize on their filter feeding lifestyle, allowing plankton and other really small creatures to flow in while preventing larger, potentially harmful animals from getting clogged inside.
This means that no human can get eaten by a whale shark or its filter feeding bretheren, the basking shark and megamouth shark. You are more likely to get eaten by a cookiecutter shark.

text:
This stream marks the End of the Beginning for me. Not only because it's their first complete 'cycle' of Group Collab stream (marking their first month as Hololive EN), but also because they'll have  collabs possibly with the JP crew at some point after this, which is kind of a dilineation point. Watching them plant their feet in Minecraft (which has always been important to Hololive group streams) is good as well. I can already imagine the 2nd gen coming to explore server down the road. So all-in-all a pretty historic stream (though I don't think they realised that given how tired they all were by the end). 

It feels great to have witnessed the start of their journey and influences some of the memes and other stuff that has developed along the way live (even if it meant messing up my sleep schedule as a cursed Euro). It's been a privaledge, and this is just the start of everything.

text:
The Five Man Band Trope applies, I think:
Gura: The Captain and Leader, who carries a map and directs the team, first of the team to make landfall. The myriad adventures and ceaseless misadventures are spurred forward by Gura. Owns a horse named Jorgen.
Amelia: The Lancer, who follows their own path and fights to their own accord while being the leader‚Äôs polar opposite. Known to be toxic and very, very hostile when provoked but still quite cooperative.
Ina: The Smart One, the most capable survivor and anchors the team‚Äôs progress. Quiet, but possibly more competent that the rest of the team combined. 
Kiara: The Heart, the most likely to die but the most uplifting and endearingly helpless of the team. Even though she dies the most, she also returns with twice the vigor than the rest can muster.
Calliope: The Big Guy, aloof, restless, and also the goddamn reaper. Physically the largest of the team and even while silent most of the time, holds an imposing posture. Not the strongest fighter but certainly the most monolithic.
